definitions.definition: To split , part ; to go away, depart .
To join , unite ; to form links between (now especially of two places in different countries); to pair with.
examples: Reading, the English town, is twinned with Clonmel in Ireland.
Coventry twinned with Dresden as an act of peace and reconciliation, both cities having been heavily bombed during the war.

definitions.definition: To be, or be like, a twin to (someone else); to match in some way.
To be, or be like, a pair of twins (for example, to dress identically); to be paired or suited.

main_definition: ( transitive , obsolete outside Scotland ) To separate , divide .
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive , obsolete outside Scotland ) To split , part ; to go away, depart .
( usually in the passive ) To join , unite ; to form links between (now especially of two places in different countries); to pair with.
( intransitive ) To give birth to twins.
( transitive ) To be, or be like, a twin to (someone else); to match in some way.
( intransitive ) To be, or be like, a pair of twins (for example, to dress identically); to be paired or suited.
